<h1 class="page-header">JS Libraries: jQuery</h1>
<blockquote>
  <p>A JavaScript library is a library of pre-written JavaScript which allows for easier development of JavaScript-based applications, especially for AJAX and other web-centric technologies.</p>
  <p>Some examples:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>jQuery</li>
    <li>Prototype JavaScript Framework</li>
    <li>Dojo Toolkit</li>
    <li>MooTools</li>
    <li>YUI Library</li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>

<h2>jQuery</h2>
<blockquote>
  <p>jQuery is by far the most popular JS library out there.</p>
  <p>It is particularly good at:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>finding elements in your HTML document</li>
    <li>changing HTML content</li>
    <li>listening to user interactions and reacting accordingly</li>
    <li>animate content on the page</li>
    <li>talk over the network to push or fetch some content</li>
  </ul>
  <h4>But that's not all.</h4>
  <p>Each browser interacts with the DOM differently. With jQuery, you can write one piece of code and not worry about the different browser and DOM interfaces.</p>
</blockquote>

